18/08/2003
TREBINJE, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Local authorities in Republika Srpska (RS) announced on Saturday (16 August) that most of the fires in the Trebinje region have been contained. RS Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic discussed the situation with the local government and decided not to call a state of natural disaster. Officials credited fast intervention by firefighting brigades with averting more serious damage. Mikerevic told the local press that the central government plans to send more equipment to support local civil protection units. He assessed damage in the region at 500,000 euros. Around 300 fires have been reported in the past month. (BH Radio 1, SRNA - 16/08/03)
